<br>
A person put to death has ZERO potential to committ another crime.<br>
<br>
A person given &quot;life without parole&quot; can still kill again, and some do.  Granted, it may be fellow inmates that get killed, but murder is still murder.<br>
<br>
A person given a number of years, or &quot;life&quot; has the potential to get out of prison.  Once out, they have the ability to kill again.<br>
<br>
